variables.value: The reunion's at that Champon store in the Arcade.\nI'm counting on you!
I swear, <FUL:SHIROYAMA> kinda looks like President <FLC:SENNO>... just a little!
Don't tell anyone I said that, okay?
Why I stopped playing football? I-I'm sorry...\nI can't say... G-goodbye.
The moment a train passes this crossing is the best feeling.\nSomeday, I'm gonna be a conductor and cross it myself.
Lots of people geek out on trains, but not many love railroad crossings\nlike I do. I want more folks to see how amazing it is\nwhen trains and people share the same path.
The tracks glowing in the sunset look so beautiful.\nThey fit this laid-back town perfectly.
Big cities mostly use electronic crossing bells now,\nbut here it's still the old gong. That sound has way more character.
Word is the occult society's investigating this place\nbecause a strange entity sometimes crosses the tracks here.
If I join the metal club, maybe I'll find some kindred spirits.\nNo one at school shares my love for railroad crossings yet.
I heard the whole school's decided to support the football club.\nIf it was a train trivia contest, I'd be all in.
No, the No. 9 West\nLine, for sure!
When you hear "No. 9 West Group," do you think trains or buses?\nFor me, it's trains, no question.
Wanna go to the shop district?
Want to hit up\nRai Rai Noodles?
I wanna check out\ntheir main store.
Isn't it a little\nearly for that?
These two spent a whole week\npicking profile pics for the school app.
Have you seen <FST:RAIKA>'s posts on the school app?\nHer pics and captions are always so on point!
I scored the new CHAMP-ON sneakers!\nCan't wait to show them off at school and totally flex!
Wait, are you actually into the new CHAMP drops, <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>?\nThat's kinda unexpected!
<FST:ITADAKI> in our class? That drive of his is next level.\nEven us fashion girls could learn a thing or two from him!
The football club's back, right? Congrats!\nSounds like a blast! We're coming to cheer, so look forward to it!
Special moves are a must, right?\nYou need something to count on when it comes down to the wire!
The Mary Times football team is totally electric!\nJust watching them gets you hyped!
Haven't <FST:RAIKA> and <LST:SAKURAZAKI> gotten even better lately?\nAlso, who knew the VP was that good at football?!
That seventh grader—<FLC:KISOJI>, right?\nLooked like he was having the time of his life!\nJust watching him pumped me up!
Football Frontier without its Football Monster just feels\nkinda empty, y'know? Wish <FUL:HARU> would make a comeback...
Your profile pic sets your whole vibe, right?\nSo... do I go for a selfie, or a pic of my idol...?
I mean, <FST:RAIKA>'s just too photogenic.\nIt's not fair... She looks amazing no matter what!
They're totally sold out online...\nI'm heading to Kool Kit in the shopping district to check there.
Wait what—<FLC:SAKURAZAKI>, actually talking to me?\nThis is like, a once-in-a-lifetime thing! What happened?!
He was pumped about a pop quiz like,\n"Perfect chance to show my skills!"\nCan you believe that mindset?!
Didn't they say football was totally taboo? And now you've\nbrought it back? You're like, the trendsetters of the school!
Wanna see my secret move? It's never failed.\nI've landed every guy I've aimed for!
When I visited Okinawa, I saw this local team practicing.\nEveryone was so into it and having a blast!
<FLC:YAGYU> still totally owns the field, huh?\nAnd <FLC:SORAMIYA> from Northbright? He's kinda good at everything?
That match with the Kinki school?\nAll those massive summons? Totally insane power levels!
I don't know the full story, but sounds like Raimon's manager just...\nquit outta nowhere.
I took a selfie on the app and <FUL:KASUMIN> was in the background.\nShe was wearing cat ears too! It was so cute!
Ugh, no update today either... Maybe <FST:RAIKA>'s over the app already.
My fave InaTuber was wearing a CHAMP hoodie...\nI think I might grab one to match!
N-No way you're into sports brands or anything like that, right?\nSorry for making a scene out here...
He's trying to start a whole new club, but like...\nthere aren't even any free advisors. What's he gonna do?
Maybe we should just join the team too?\nCute girls who can crush it at football—that's like, peak power.
I'm working on a killer move to snag my crush... Wanna train with me?
Ughhh I'm so jealous of those kids.\nLiving the student life on a tropical island? Literal dream.
<FST:KAMEO>'s footwork is unreal!\nHis speed is the stuff of legends!
How do you even learn to use a Keshin, anyway?\nImagine bringing that out for a pic. You'd steal the spotlight!
The newest Eleven mag's sold out everywhere!\nThe hype's totally got that pre-final buzz!
You should totally\nmake that your profile pic.
I went to Kool Kit\nfor it.
Think it's doable if he\nfinds a teacher?
Guess I'll just have to\nmake one up!
Gonna show off\nwhat practice can do?
No way! I'm fast\nlike the wind!
From that store in\nthe shopping district?
I wanna ask how\nhe runs so fast!
Hey, there a big guy at your school toting around a big backpack?\nHe was crazy fast, and I wanna know his secret!
You're big too, but you're not the one I'm looking for.\nI'm looking for a big guy with a big backpack!
Mommy, I really, really,\nreally want to know...
But I'm so, so,\nso, so curious!
And I'm so, so,\nso, so clueless.
They say this little stream has been here forever.\nBut why'd they build it right in the middle of the road?
They say this town's got a ton of hills.\nHow'd it end up with terrain like that?
Trams are pretty rare these days, right?\nSo why's there one here in <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>?
I heard some people talking about "gangs" earlier.\nSounded like they're bad guys, but what does it really mean?
Why do some schools say "private" and some say "public"?\nWhat's the difference?
They say lots of rich people live at Hillview Terrace.\nWhy do they all live in the same place?
I heard <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> is a port town, so it's full of cats.\nBut why cats? Why not other animals?
They say hydrangeas are the town flower in Nagasaki.\nBut there are so many flowers—why that one?
I heard foreign ships used to come to <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> Port\na long time ago. Why this town, though?
How does the Skycraft even fly? It's made of metal! Isn't that weird?
Kids this age ask the hardest questions...\nTheir curiosity is astounding, let me tell you.
My boy's questions are beyond me...\nI don't know how to answer...\nMaybe I should just look up the answers online...
I've tried looking up his questions online,\nbut the answers are so complicated...\nIt's tough figuring out how to explain them in kid terms.
I don't really want to teach him about stuff like that, but...\na gang's just people doing shady things. Not exactly legal.
<MNT:NAGUMOHARA> and West Manor are private schools, right?\nI went to public school, so I don't know a ton about private ones...
Kids always ask the kinds of questions grown-ups never think about...\nI wonder how other moms handle this stuff.
My son asks stuff that never even crosses my mind...\nand when I stop to think about it, I don't know half the answers.
Kids get curious about everything.\nLately the questions are so tough,\neven looking up the answers is a full-time job!
Back then, there were only a few ports foreign ships could visit.\nBut if you ask me why... I'm not really sure how to explain it.
My kid wants to know everything.\nLately, I swear he knows more than I do...
I'll study so hard he won't even recognize me!\nI'll make him eat his words on the next exam!
He said we'll settle things next time in gym class!\nThink he got worked up after watching your football face-off?
We had words, and I placed my bet on the football club.\nJust do me a favor and make sure it's a tie, at least!
He's actually been paying a lot of attention to <FST:RAIKA> lately...\nOf course, it goes without saying that <FST:RAIKA>'s a total cutie!
I can't believe I ended up at the same school as <FLC:SHINANO>!\nHonestly, he's way more grown-up than that guy will ever be...
I wish I'd signed up to volunteer at the Football Gardens!\nHonestly, he seemed kinda interested in going too...
He summoned me to the base of the God Tree.\nWhat could he be scheming this time?
I swear I'm the smartest here!\nI must be, or else... she'll never even notice me.
I'm following your example and getting serious about exercise!\nIf it's P.E., I might actually be able to get the best of her...
I made a bet with my crush on the outcome of a football match.\nSo if I win the bet... I'm thinking of telling her how I feel.
She's crazy about the football club, so I'm pushing myself\nto stay updated with the latest news...
Sounds like she's a fan of one of the Northbright players.\nGuys in powerhouse clubs are even popular with kids at other schools...
I heard the Northbright kids are moving into an old school building.\n...I feel a bit better now knowing that.
I got the volunteer forms for the Football Gardens...\nbut I couldn't work up the courage to invite her.
I decided to finally share my feelings with my crush.\nI think the God Tree's power might help me get the words out...
Ack! You caught me while I was wiping up the coffee I spilled!
(I see now. That's no Kraken. That has to be...)
(Either way, I'm not entertaining this Kraken farce anymore.)
<FUL:UMIBOZU>... Huh. It's just standing there.\nMight be a good chance to get a photo.
Aren't we jumping\nthe gun a bit?
I almost want to\nlearn from them.
I wonder if the potatoes\nwill be okay.
Maybe we should shade\nthem with a net...
That might be going\na little too far...
Maybe I should grab a study guide from the shopping district...\nBut I don't want to waste a single second of my study time.
I'm trying to decide which study guide to get...\nThe bookstore has such a great selection,\nI always end up buying way too many.
I wonder which university <FLA:GARYU> is aiming for.\nHe's a master at classical poetry—\nprobably something in literature.
When it comes to mock tests in Kyushu, students from <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>,\nWest Manor, or Eastwind Peregrine are always battling for the top spots.
Wait, you're that guy—the one who stood up to <FLC:YAGYU>!\nI'd show more respect for those in power if I were you.
I'm not the gutsy type like you.\nJust hanging out with cats like this is enough for me.
W-wait, <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>?! Why are you talking to me?\nI'm a peaceful guy who doesn't get in anyone's way—\nso no worries, okay?
Staying out of faction feuds and power struggles is the safest bet!\nYou get that, right? Just leave me alone...!
Not just <FLC:YAGYU>... you even dragged the student council into this.\nAre you, like, hungry for power or something?
You actually got the whole school to back the football club?\nPresident <FLC:SENNO>'s football reforms are something else.
Some people complain about the merger,\nbut griping about what the board decided won't change a thing.
Switching campuses now? Seriously?\nI just can't get motivated unless I'm in my usual classroom.
Odaiba Football Gardens? Too many distractions there.\nIf I was on the team, I'd totally ditch practice and mess around.
<FLC:SHINANO> and <FLC:TOMOBE> are killing it. Mad respect. Me? Not so much...
Maybe a private tutor could fix my habit of slacking off...\nMight as well try BrightPath Tutoring.
